review_blob: A good ale,smoothe and crisp,a bit of smoke makes it tasty.An easy drinkable brew.
Not the kind of porter Im used to.There was no head to be seen,and a kind of burnt chocolate flavor killed any chance of a good finish.
Fruity and spicy,this brew isnt bad.It had a dry finish which was not too over-powered by the alcohol.
Sweet honey flavor does not overpower the strong alcohol aroma.Not a terribly bad mead.I found it an interesitng one time try.
Nice and strong,but too sweet and the alcohol taste lingered after the finish.Ill have a few of these laying around for a while,so Ill try it again in the future.[possible re-rate?]
Ilove hops,and thats the thing that this ale is missing.I like the malt sweetness,but is on the verge of being too sweet.
This is a super smooth beer,very clean and a definet buy again.
This brew caught my attention,it had a rich, fruity flavor,and a nice clean finish.
Ilove hops!This beer is sharp and has a long lasting finish.
Strong coffee like hues give this stout a good depth.
